## Bug

**Target**
Tested on EFM32PG12 with LowPowerTicker

**Toolchain:**
GCC_ARM

**Toolchain version:**
6-2017-q2-update

**mbed-cli version:** 
1.3.0

**mbed-os sha:**
caeaa49d68c67ee00275cece10cd88e0ed0f6ed3

**Expected behavior**

When the system goes into `error()`, all threads and tickers should be stopped. Relevant for watchdog feeding / kicking.

**Actual behavior**

Threads and Tickers continue to execute and feed watchdog, preventing it from resetting the board.

**Steps to reproduce**

Ticker
```
#include "mbed.h"

DigitalOut led(LED1);
LowPowerTicker watchdogTicker;

void watchdogRefreshIsr() {
    led = !led;
    // target-specific feed function
};

int main() {
    watchdogTicker.attach(callback(&watchdogRefreshIsr), 0.5f);
}
```

Thread
```
#include "mbed.h"

DigitalOut led(LED1);
LowPowerTicker watchdogTicker;
Thread watchdogThread;
EventQueue watchdogQueue;

void watchdogRefreshHandler() {
    led = !led;
    // target-specific feed function
};

void watchdogRefreshIsr() {
    watchdogQueue.call(callback(&watchdogRefreshHandler));
};

int main() {
    watchdogThread.start(callback(&watchdogQueue, &EventQueue::dispatch_forever));
    watchdogTicker.attach(callback(&watchdogRefreshIsr), 0.5f);
}
```

